<title type="html"><![CDATA[Something I noticed while making tiles.]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=7678&amp;p=77131#p77131"><![CDATA[
The problem is that you added the shadow below the grass but did not shade/light the sides of the rocks. Try darkening their left side and highlighting their right side and you'll see they'll look pretty solid, and much more interesting than the flat picture.<br /><br />If you want your graphics to have depth, you can't be stingy with the tiles, you need to make different edges for the different sides because depending on the light source each side will look slightly different.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=95">tokumaru</a> — Sat Apr 23, 2011 11:45 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
