<title type="html"><![CDATA[Something I noticed while making tiles.]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=7678&amp;p=77128#p77128"><![CDATA[
I was switching my game over from some "borrowed" place holder graphics to some more proper homemade graphics when I noticed something.<br /><br />With Shadow:<br /><img src="http://farm6.static.flickr.com/5221/5646524441_7a3e6dc8bf.jpg" alt="Image" /><br /><br />Without Shadow:<br /><img src="http://farm6.static.flickr.com/5227/5646530255_0f6cb0229c.jpg" alt="Image" /><br /><br />To me, the image with the shadow from the grass conveys the ability to pass through the rocks.  For example, you could be standing on the grass and then jump down to another platform with the rocks in the background.<br /><br />The shadowless image, however, feels solid.  It looks like you couldn't pass through it at all.<br /><br />Just food for thought, I guess?<br /><br />I'm still not satisfied with these tiles at all and I'll keep working, but if anyone is interested in anymore of the stuff, I'll certainly post again!  Also, I'd be interested if anyone else had any thoughts on graphic composition.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=4250">Ian A</a> — Sat Apr 23, 2011 11:26 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
